                <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
                    <StackPanel MaxWidth="460">
                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10">
                            Mahjong is a 4-player game that originated in China, and is now played around the world. 
                            The rules can vary from country to country, region to region, even family to family.
                        </TextBlock>
                        
                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,0,0,10"> 
                            Playing Mahjong is simple, but the scoring rules can be a bit complicated. 
                            This app is meant to help with that. 
                            It calculates scores for each round, keeps track of everyone's scores, and teaches you how to play the game. 
                            The app uses a classical rule set (based on a book from the 1960s called 'A Mahjong Handbook') which is described in this app.  
                            But it's flexible enough to accommodate some rule variations, such as the starting score and the value of a limit hand (which can be adjusted when you begin a new game).
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,0,0,10">
                            Mahjong Aid will keep track of ongoing and completed games. 
                            When you save a game, you can load it from your Windows PC, tablet, or phone. 
                            If you already know how to score and just want to use this app to keep track of games, you can enter your round scores manually.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,0,0,10">
                            Swipe over to learn more about how to play Mahjong and how to use this app.
                        </TextBlock>
                    </StackPanel>
                </ScrollViewer>
