            <PivotItem Header="Setting Up">
                <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
                    <StackPanel MaxWidth="460">

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10"> 
                           To begin a game, you first need to choose each player's starting position. 
                            Find the East, South, West, and North tiles and place them upside down:
                        </TextBlock>

                        <StackPanel Orientation="Horizontal" HorizontalAlignment="Center">
                            <FontIcon FontFamily="Segoe UI Emoji" 
                                      Margin="5,0"
                                      FontSize="40"
                                      Glyph="&#x1F000;" />
                            <FontIcon FontFamily="Segoe UI Emoji" 
                                      Margin="5,0"
                                      FontSize="40"
                                      Glyph="&#x1F001;" />
                            <FontIcon FontFamily="Segoe UI Emoji" 
                                      Margin="5,0"
                                      FontSize="40"
                                      Glyph="&#x1F002;" />
                            <FontIcon FontFamily="Segoe UI Emoji" 
                                      Margin="5,0"
                                      FontSize="40"
                                      Glyph="&#x1F003;" />                           
                        </StackPanel>

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10"> 
                            Each player chooses a tile. 
                            The player who picks East is the starting dealer, and the other players' winds are their starting lucky winds. 
                            Players sit around the table like so:                         
                        </TextBlock>

                        <Grid HorizontalAlignment="Center">
                            <Grid.RowDefinitions>
                                <RowDefinition Height="115"/>
                                <RowDefinition Height="115"/>
                                <RowDefinition Height="115"/>
                            </Grid.RowDefinitions>
                            <Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
                                <ColumnDefinition Width="115" />
                                <ColumnDefinition Width="115" />
                                <ColumnDefinition Width="115" />
                            </Grid.ColumnDefinitions>

                            <StackPanel Margin="5" 
                                        Grid.Row="1" 
                                        Grid.Column="2">

                                <FontIcon FontFamily="Segoe UI Emoji"
                                          Glyph="&#x1F000;" 
                                          FontSize="30" />

                                <TextBlock Style="{ThemeResource PlayerNameTextBlockStyle}"
                                           Text="East Player" />
                            </StackPanel>

                            <StackPanel Margin="5" 
                                        Grid.Row="0" 
                                        Grid.Column="1">

                                <FontIcon FontFamily="Segoe UI Emoji"
                                          Glyph="&#x1F001;" 
                                          FontSize="30" />

                                <TextBlock Style="{ThemeResource PlayerNameTextBlockStyle}"
                                           Text="South Player" />
                            </StackPanel>

                            <StackPanel Margin="5" 
                            Grid.Row="1" 
                            Grid.Column="0">

                                <FontIcon FontFamily="Segoe UI Emoji"
                                          Glyph="&#x1F002;" 
                                          FontSize="30" />

                                <TextBlock Style="{ThemeResource PlayerNameTextBlockStyle}"
                                           Text="West Player" />

                            </StackPanel>

                            <StackPanel Margin="5" 
                                        Grid.Row="2" 
                                        Grid.Column="1">

                                <FontIcon FontFamily="Segoe UI Emoji"
                                          Glyph="&#x1F003;" 
                                          FontSize="30" />

                                <TextBlock Style="{ThemeResource PlayerNameTextBlockStyle}"
                                           Text="North Player" />

                            </StackPanel>
                        </Grid>

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10"> 
                            Every round begins by stirring the tiles on the table and setting up the four walls. 
                            Shuffle the wind tiles back into the pile, then stack the tiles in 4 walls (17 tiles long, 2 tiles high) around the table, like so:
                        </TextBlock>
                        
                        <Image Source="/Assets/learn-to-play/four-walls-start.png" />

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10">                            
                            The East player then rolls the two dice. 
                            Starting on the right side of the East wall, the dealer counts tiles the number rolled on the dice, counter-clockwise. 
                            For example, if they rolled a 7, they count 7 tiles along the top of the wall, and take the stack of 2 tiles, like so:
                        </TextBlock>

                        <Image Source="/Assets/learn-to-play/four-walls-dice-roll.png" />

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10">
                            This space marks where the dealing will begin (to the left), and where the Dead Wall is (to the right).
                            The dealer places the 2 tiles upside-down on top of the Dead Wall.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <Image Source="/Assets/learn-to-play/dead-wall.png" />

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10">
                            Then, they deal tiles in in groups of 4 around the table, starting with themself. 
                            They continue until each player has 12 tiles. 
                            Lastly, they take 2 more tiles for themself, and deal 1 additional tile to each other player. 
                            (The dealer begins the game with an extra tile, which is their first draw tile.)
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10">
                            The table should look something like this:
                        </TextBlock>

                        <Image Source="/Assets/learn-to-play/four-walls-tiles-dealt.png" />

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10">
                            That's it! Each player has 13 tiles, and the dealer has 13 tiles plus their first draw tile.
                            You're ready to play a round.
                        </TextBlock>

                    </StackPanel>
                </ScrollViewer>
