            <PivotItem Header="Playing a Round">
                <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
                    <StackPanel MaxWidth="460">

                        <TextBlock Text="Round Flow" 
                                   Margin="0,10,0,5" 
                                   Foreground="{ThemeResource MahjongAccentColorBrush}" 
                                   FontWeight="SemiBold" 
                                   FontSize="22" />


                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10"> 
                            Game play for each round goes around the table counter-clockwise, starting with the dealer. 
                            Since the dealer took an extra tile during setup, they don't need to draw a tile. 
                            Instead, they just choose a tile to discard. 
                            For the rest of the round, players draw a tile from the wall, then choose a tile to discard.
                            Tiles are always discarded face up, and players always end a round with 13 tiles.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10"> 
                            Here's a game in progress:
                        </TextBlock>

                        <Image Source="/Assets/learn-to-play/game-in-progress.png" />

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10"> 
                            This game is on it's 3rd time around the table, so the dealer has just discarded their 3rd tile. 
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock Text="Sets and Pairs" 
                                   Margin="0,20,0,5" 
                                   Foreground="{ThemeResource MahjongAccentColorBrush}" 
                                   FontWeight="SemiBold" 
                                   FontSize="22" />

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10"> 
                            The first player to "go out" says "Mahjong!", and wins the round. 
                            A winning Mahjong hand usually consists of four sets and one pair. 
                            Pairs are simple: They consist of two of the same tile.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10"> 
                            An example of a Pair:
                        </TextBlock>
                        <StackPanel Orientation="Horizontal">
                            <FontIcon FontFamily="Segoe UI Emoji"
                                      Glyph="&#x1F000;" 
                                      Margin="0,0,5,0"
                                      FontSize="30" />
                            <FontIcon FontFamily="Segoe UI Emoji"
                                      Glyph="&#x1F000;" 
                                      FontSize="30" />
                        </StackPanel>

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10"> 
                            Sets, on the other hand, are varied. 
                            There are three types of sets: A Chow (run of 3 tiles), a Pung (3 of the same tile), and a Kong (4 of the same tile).
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10"> 
                            An example of a Chow:
                        </TextBlock>
                        <StackPanel Orientation="Horizontal">
                            <FontIcon FontFamily="Segoe UI Emoji"
                                      Glyph="&#x1F009;" 
                                      Margin="0,0,5,0"
                                      FontSize="30" />
                            <FontIcon FontFamily="Segoe UI Emoji"
                                      Glyph="&#x1F00A;" 
                                      Margin="0,0,5,0"
                                      FontSize="30" />
                            <FontIcon FontFamily="Segoe UI Emoji"
                                      Glyph="&#x1F00B;" 
                                      FontSize="30" />
                        </StackPanel>

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10"> 
                            An example of a Pung:
                        </TextBlock>
                        <StackPanel Orientation="Horizontal">
                            <FontIcon FontFamily="Segoe UI Emoji"
                                      Glyph="&#x1F011;" 
                                      Margin="0,0,5,0"
                                      FontSize="30" />
                            <FontIcon FontFamily="Segoe UI Emoji"
                                      Glyph="&#x1F011;" 
                                      Margin="0,0,5,0"
                                      FontSize="30" />
                            <FontIcon FontFamily="Segoe UI Emoji"
