                        <TextBlock Text="Ending a Round" 
                                   Margin="0,20,0,5" 
                                   Foreground="{ThemeResource MahjongAccentColorBrush}" 
                                   FontWeight="SemiBold" 
                                   FontSize="22" />

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10"> 
                            A round ends when a player either steals their winning tile or draws it from the wall, and calls "Mahjong!" 
                            If two players both call Mahjong on the same discard tile, the one closest to the discarder wins the tie-breaker. 
                            The winning hand is scored, the losers pay the winner, and then the tiles are stirred and another round begins.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10"> 
                            This app keeps track of a lot of details so you don't have to, such as who is dealing a given round, each players' lucky wind, and the round's prevailing wind. 
                            Read on if you want to understand how it all works, or just use the app and ignore this stuff.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10"> 
                            If the dealer wins, they get to deal again. 
                            If someone else wins, the person to the right deals the next round. 
                            Since the dealer's Lucky Wind is always East, all the players' Lucky Winds rotate around the table counter-clockwise when the dealer changes. 
                            East player becomes North, South becomes East, West becomes South, and North becomes West.
                        </TextBlock>
                        <Image Source="/Assets/learn-to-play/wind-rotation.png" />

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,0,0,30"> 
                            there's also the Prevailing Wind to keep track of. 
                            The game always begins with East as the Prevailing Wind, and it stays that way until dealer duty has made it around the table and the original dealer deals again. 
                            At that point, Prevailing Wind changes from East to South (then West, then North). 
                            For example: If the dealer doesn't win any of the first four rounds, Prevailing Wind would shift from East to South on the fifth round. 
                            But if the dealer won the second round, the Prevailing Wind wouldn't change until the sixth round.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock Text="Winning the Game" 
                                   Margin="0,20,0,5" 
                                   Foreground="{ThemeResource MahjongAccentColorBrush}" 
                                   FontWeight="SemiBold" 
                                   FontSize="22" />

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10"> 
                            The game ends when every player has dealt 4 times, and the Prevailing Wind has been all four winds. 
                            This will be a minimum of 16 rounds, though it's usually more, since dealer duty doesn't change if the dealer wins. 
                            The player with the most points at the end wins the game. 
                        </TextBlock>
                    </StackPanel>
